    {
      "id": "pt_030",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "### PT-030 closed\n\nSpecialist agent selection and scenario-specific expert roles are not explicit\n\nNode: decision_recommendation",
      "x": 720,
      "y": 1470,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 190
    },
    {
      "id": "pt_031",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "### PT-031 open\n\nProactive process scheduling lacks real-world cadence, culture context, second interaction, invitation and meeting strategy loops\n\nNode: trigger_plan",
      "x": 1080,
      "y": 1470,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 190
    },
    {
      "id": "pt028_event_feedback_acceptance_artifacts",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## PT-028 event/feedback/acceptance artifacts\n\nCommands:\n- npm run pt028:event-stream\n- npm run pt028:event-stream -- --session=runtime/pt028-feedback-collection-sessions/latest.json\n- npm run pt028:event-stream -- --feedback=runtime/user-inputs/pt028-real-multi-window-operator-feedback.real.json\n- npm run pt028:feedback-decision-pack\n- npm run pt028:feedback-handoff:validate\n- npm run pt028:feedback-collection:session\n- npm run pt028:feedback-collection:coverage\n- npm run pt028:feedback-finalize -- --decision=<decision template path>\n- npm run pt028:feedback-confirm:preflight\n- npm run pt028:acceptance-status\n- npm run pt028:operator-handoff\n- npm run pt028:operator-handoff:refresh\n- npm run pt028:acceptance-chain\n\nStatus: low-latency event stream, collection-session multi-window prebinding, feedback-bound multi-window event stream mode, real feedback workpack, controlled confirmation gate, finalization runner, read-only acceptance status with event counts/input-mode/latency/prompt-only summary, operator acceptance handoff with pt028_operator_quickstart.v1, operator handoff refresh chain, feedback collection handoff/session/coverage summary and final acceptance chain are wired. Production remains blocked pending human-reviewed real operator feedback and final human special review.",
      "x": 0,
      "y": -560,
      "width": 760,
      "height": 460
    },
    {
      "id": "process_tree_validation_governance",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Process Tree Sync Rule\n\nRun npm run process-tree:validate after changing docs/15, examples/system-process-tree.json, views/obsidian/system-process-tree.md or views/obsidian/system-process-tree.canvas.\n\nRequired views:\n- docs/15-????????????.md\n- examples/system-process-tree.json\n- views/obsidian/system-process-tree.md\n- views/obsidian/system-process-tree.canvas",
      "x": 820,
      "y": -560,
      "width": 620,
      "height": 330
    },
    {
      "id": "pt028_real_feedback_finalizations",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## runtime/pt028-real-feedback-finalizations/**\n\nOutput of npm run pt028:feedback-finalize.\n\nContains ordered finalization reports, per-step artifacts, target-write status, feedback-bound event stream, readiness, calibration, acceptance-chain evidence and no-send boundary.",
      "x": 1480,
      "y": -560,
      "width": 520,
      "height": 260
    },
    {
      "id": "pt028_event_stream_health",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## runtime/pt028-event-stream-health/**\n\nOutput of npm run pt028:event-stream:health.\n\nValidates the PT-028 GUI event stream low-latency subscription contract: IPC channel, 50ms dispatch, 50ms debounce, 1s fallback poll, event sequence integrity, window/target coverage, prompt-only and no-send boundary.",
      "x": 2040,
      "y": -560,
      "width": 560,
      "height": 280
    },
    {
      "id": "pt028_final_special_review_pack",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## runtime/pt028-final-special-review-packs/**\n\nOutput of npm run pt028:final-review-pack.\n\nConsolidates decision pack, collection session, event-stream health, finalization and acceptance-chain evidence into a human special review handoff. The handoff exposes event-stream input/count/latency/prompt-only summary, feedback collection session/coverage/confirmed-task summary and window-task-to-template-row mapping. Read-only; no send; no target write.",
      "x": 2640,
      "y": -560,
      "width": 600,
      "height": 300
    },
    {
      "id": "pt028_human_review_decision_writer",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## runtime/pt028-human-review-decisions/**\n\nOutput of npm run pt028:human-review-decision.\n\nWrites a fillable human review sheet JSON plus Markdown/HTML worksheet by default. The JSON sheet embeds pt028_human_review_sheet_guidance.v1 and pt028_human_review_evidence_summary.v1 for allowed decisions, response signals, row-ready rules, final-review rules, event-stream evidence, feedback-collection progress and the safe completion sequence. The writer report also exposes template_initial_diagnostics and pt028_human_review_fill_plan.v1 for the unfilled sheet so GUI or external filling tools can see target files, row-level fill tasks, missing confirmations, command order and row failures before human input. With --review --check-only, missing requested review files produce human_review_sheet_input_missing plus pt028_review_sheet_input_status.v1; present review files produce diagnostics without generating a decision. With --review, converts the filled sheet into a confirmation decision JSON for coverage, preflight and finalization. Read-only for the real feedback target; no send.",
      "x": 3280,
      "y": -560,
      "width": 620,
      "height": 300
    },
    {
      "id": "pt028_acceptance_statuses",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## runtime/pt028-acceptance-statuses/**\n\nOutput of npm run pt028:acceptance-status.\n\nRead-only current-status snapshots for low-latency event stream counts/input-mode/latency/prompt-only summary, feedback-bound multi-window evidence, real feedback readiness, real feedback calibration, final human review handoff with JSON/Markdown/HTML worksheet paths, handoff freshness against latest source artifacts, review-sheet initial diagnostics summary, pt028_human_review_fill_plan_summary.v1, pt028_operator_action_queue.v1 current/next blocking action ids, stable human input target paths, remaining blockers and next commands. It does not rerun the chain, write the real feedback target, approve review or send messages.",
      "x": 3920,
      "y": -560,
      "width": 620,
      "height": 320
    },
    {
      "id": "pt028_operator_acceptance_handoffs",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## runtime/pt028-operator-acceptance-handoffs/**\n\nOutput of npm run pt028:operator-handoff.\n\nRead-only final operator handoff from the latest acceptance status, final special review pack and human review sheet. It exposes pt028_operator_quickstart.v1 for the first action, open paths, target files and command order, passes through pt028_operator_action_queue.v1 for current/next blocking action ids, then summarizes event-stream evidence, feedback collection coverage, pending human actions and the no target-write/no-send/no-approval boundary.",
      "x": 4580,
      "y": -560,
      "width": 620,
      "height": 300
    },
    {
      "id": "pt028_operator_handoff_refresh_chains",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## runtime/pt028-operator-handoff-refresh-chains/**\n\nOutput of npm run pt028:operator-handoff:refresh.\n\nOrdered read-only refresh report. When a real feedback target exists, it runs feedback-bound acceptance-chain first, then refreshes final-review-pack, human-review-decision template/check-only, optional auto controlled preflight, acceptance-status and operator-handoff so human review materials bind the latest acceptance-chain evidence. It auto-detects runtime/user-inputs/pt028-human-review-decision.real.json for check-only, runs controlled preflight when that default review is ready, exposes pt028_controlled_preflight_summary.v1 with generated decision output and exact finalization command, exposes pt028_human_review_fill_plan_summary.v1 with target files, row-level fill state, unready rows and command order, exposes pt028_operator_action_queue_summary.v1 with current action, next blocking action and action statuses, and auto-detects runtime/user-inputs/pt028-real-multi-window-operator-feedback.real.json for read-only acceptance-chain validation when present. It exposes per-step gates, pt028_operator_quickstart_summary.v1, latest artifact refs, human input target status, review/feedback input detection and no finalization/no target-write/no-send boundary.",
      "x": 5240,
      "y": -560,
      "width": 620,
      "height": 300
    },
    {
      "id": "pt028_operator_next_steps",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## runtime/pt028-operator-next-steps/**\n\nOutput of npm run pt028:operator-next-step.\n\nRead-only current action report from the latest refresh chain, operator handoff and acceptance status. It exposes pt028_operator_next_step.v1, pt028_operator_objective_progress.v1 tracks and pt028_operator_completion_gate.v1 fail-on-incomplete evidence for low-latency event stream, real multi-window feedback calibration and final special acceptance, normalized queue, current action, next blocking action, target status, next commands and source artifact refs. npm run pt028:operator-next-step:check exits non-zero until the active goal is actually complete. Sightflow GUI reads this through zhineng:decision-state:get, keeps the dock short status as R*/O*/F* · current_turn_intent · gate_status, and shows Acceptance Gate blockers without writing runtime/user-inputs/** or sending messages. It does not run finalization, write runtime/user-inputs/**, approve review or send messages.",
      "x": 5900,
      "y": -560,
      "width": 620,
      "height": 300
    },
    {
      "id": "capability_upgrade_registry",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## capability_upgrade_registry\n\n能力升级候选库\n\nStores excellent external projects, patrols current execution modes, decomposes process IO, evaluates replacement value, and exposes source-only 3D OS projection.\n\nPaths:\n- capability-upgrade-registry/README.md\n- scripts/run-capability-upgrade-patrol.mjs\n- runtime/capability-upgrade-patrols/**\n- capability-upgrade-registry/os-particle-projection.json\n\nBoundary: read-only by default; real replacement requires IO consistency, latency/effectiveness evidence, analogical candidate confirmation, dry-run, tests, rollback, previous-requirements alignment and human confirmation.",
      "x": 4600,
      "y": -920,
      "width": 620,
      "height": 340
    },
    {
      "id": "dialogue_system_patrol",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## dialogue_system_patrol\n\nDialogue System Patrol\n\nStrict required patrol coverage, source_hash/source drift detection, scaffold entry, patrol-maintainer workflow, dialogue read index, status cards, status events, validation reports and source-only 3D projection.\n\nPaths:\n- dialogue-system-patrol/README.md\n- dialogue-system-patrol/docs/strict-governance-and-surfaces.md\n- dialogue-system-patrol/docs/module-onboarding-gate.md\n- dialogue-system-patrol/registry/system-patrol-registry.json\n- dialogue-system-patrol/blocks/**\n- dialogue-system-patrol/scripts/check-source-drift.mjs\n- dialogue-system-patrol/scripts/scaffold-module-patrol.mjs\n- dialogue-system-patrol/scripts/run-patrol-maintainer.mjs\n- dialogue-system-patrol/scripts/publish-patrol-surfaces.mjs\n- runtime/dialogue-system-patrol-source-drift/**\n- runtime/dialogue-system-patrol/dialogue-read-index.json\n- runtime/dialogue-system-patrol-maintenance/**\n- .githooks/pre-commit\n- .github/workflows/system-patrol.yml\n- dialogue-system-patrol/os-particle-projection.json\n\nBoundary: strict coverage and source drift validate patrol evidence only; no business-code rewrite; no dialogue reader source rewrite; 3D projection is source-only; no external action.",
      "x": 5260,
      "y": -1280,
      "width": 620,
      "height": 430
    },
    {
      "id": "relationship_event_storage_plan",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Relationship/Event Graph Storage Plans\n\nFormal plan entry for relationship graph, event graph and data collection storage.\n\nPaths:\n- docs/18-relationship-event-graph-memory-plan.md\n- docs/19-source-collection-classified-storage-plan.md\n- docs/20-relationship-event-graph-phased-execution-plan.md\n\nRuntime:\n- npm run relationship-event:phases\n- npm run relationship-event:p10-shadow\n- npm run relationship-event:promotion-confirmation\n- npm run relationship-event:promotion-confirmation:validate\n- npm run relationship-event:validate\n\nScope: local SourceArchive, SourceEpisode, semantic NestedEvent, SummaryShard, rule-based WeightProfile, V0-V5 visual weight levels, P10 LearningWeightShadowReport, LearningWeightPromotionConfirmation and read-only NebulaProjection.\n\nBoundary: P10 is shadow-only; promotion confirmation opens review only; no direct relationship-state write, identity merge, learning-weight promotion, limited trial execution or external action.",
      "x": 5920,
      "y": -1280,
      "width": 640,
      "height": 360
    },
    {
      "id": "intake_implementation_audit_artifacts",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Intake Implementation Audit Artifacts\n\nDocs/16 intake and controlled-send audit registration.\n\nScripts:\n- scripts/audit-intake-implementation.mjs\n- scripts/write-controlled-send-command-draft.mjs\n- scripts/confirm-controlled-send-command.mjs\n- scripts/write-controlled-send-operator-pack.mjs\n- scripts/check-controlled-send-command.mjs\n- scripts/complete-controlled-send-trial.mjs\n- scripts/write-controlled-send-handoff.mjs\n- scripts/write-docs16-implementation-status.mjs\n- scripts/bridge-tool-intake.mjs\n- scripts/init-source-adapter-kit.mjs\n- scripts/validate-source-adapter-conformance.mjs\n- scripts/init-controlled-send-material-kit.mjs\n- scripts/check-controlled-send-real-window-readiness.mjs\n\nRuntime:\n- runtime/tool-intake-bridges/**\n- runtime/controlled-send-material-kits/**\n- runtime/controlled-send-command-drafts/**\n- runtime/controlled-send-command-confirmations/**\n- runtime/controlled-send-operator-packs/**\n- runtime/controlled-send-real-window-readiness/**\n- runtime/desktop-controlled-send-command-preflights/**\n- runtime/desktop-controlled-send-handoffs/**\n- runtime/docs16-implementation-status/**\n- runtime/source-adapter-kits/**\n- runtime/source-adapter-conformance/**\n- runtime/desktop-controlled-send-completions/**\n- runtime/intake-implementation-audits/**",
      "x": 6580,
      "y": -1280,
      "width": 640,
      "height": 540
    },
    {
      "id": "cloud_source_mirror",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## cloud_source_mirror\n\nCloud Source Mirror\n\nGitHub remote: huay7380-beep/zy\n\nPaths:\n- docs/21-cloud-github-sync-plan.md\n- schemas/cloud-source-mirror.schema.json\n- scripts/write-cloud-sync-manifest.mjs\n- runtime/cloud-sync/**\n\nBoundary: source-first Git mirror; excludes third_party, node_modules, runtime outputs, tmp, .env files, model weights, binary libraries, generated logs and caches. Push requires authenticated command-line Git for huay7380-beep.",
      "x": 7240,
      "y": -1280,
      "width": 640,
      "height": 380
    }
